Officially moved from Victoria to Maple Bay! Vancouver Island 🏝️ 
I have been asked by many “why?” And the truth is I fell in love with the old heritage house but not the city!
I adore Vancouver Island but not the metro!
It was fun when I was younger and I really thought I would enjoy being back and all I felt was white noise and sounds of metro life that wasn’t me anymore.
Moving is a huge amount of work but we did it! 
Time to get back into the swing of things and get colourful in this brand extremely white newly built home!

Recreate, restyle & recycle new design and add fun styles with new colour schemes!
This Saturday’s YouTube video is about having fun with your own pieces and home decor that you can easily transform!
Full video coming Feb 4/23
YouTube link in the bio.

Exploring colours!!
Full YouTube video, link in the bio!
I had an amazing time with three talented friends that share their passion with others to bring success to your projects by sharing their stories and experiences with furniture design!
We did a creator colour challenge by each of us randomly picking a colour from Annie Sloan’s colour collection and working with only those colours plus one neutral colour tone!
From Giverny blue, Scandinavian Pink, Louis Blue & Antibes Green was the random colour that were selected and we only worked within those colours!
Exploring all the different shades and mixing the different colours together it was really fun to see what each of us would create!
The endless possibilities of random combinations!!
Check out @kachafurniture 
@jonathonmarcmendes_paintedlove

Layers are steps and taking small steps to a room makeover is all about steps!
I like to start by shapes that move a square room around and create movement first. 
Then I can work on dimensions, colours and sizes etc.
Once you start your first step it can become addictive and super fun!
It’s okay not to be happy with your individual steps but it’s easy to correct them to suit your goals and styles!! 
I am loving my first step and will share my next one soon!
